\cf0 Together they give you redundant access to the Hubble flow with 
\f0\b completely different systematic dependencies
\f1\b0  \'97 different host morphologies, different calibration chains, different inclination/aperture nuisances, different selection effects. The H0DN paper's framework uses both to provide a Hubble-flow constraint that's robust against either method's individual failure modes.\
}